    public class DBTable
extends com.vaadin.ui.Table
implements PagingComponent.IPagedComponent, ICommitable

    A custom Vaadin table made to display a portion of data from database. Supports various page sizes and paging controls to allow navigation.

    Should only be used from DBTableLayout - it knows best how to use this class.

    Author:
    SkyCrawl

      • onPageChanged

        public void onPageChanged(int page)
        Description copied from interface: PagingComponent.IPagedComponent
        Callback for when user selects another page. When this method finishes, #getAllItemsCount is called to update the paging component further.
        RED ALERT: do not EVER update paging in this method. The component updates itself as needed.
        Specified by:
        onPageChanged in interface PagingComponent.IPagedComponent

      • setView

        public void setView(AbstractDBViewRoot<? extends AbstractTableDBView> viewRoot)

        Maps a certain "database table" to this Vaadin table. Paging then determines the actual rows viewed.

        This is the most important method. Without it, the table is but an empty shell.
